Mexican Stocks: Asur, Cemex Shares Advance; America Movil Drops

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-03-08T22:43:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/mexican-stocks-cemex-penoles-shares-climb-grupo-mexico-drops.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index rose 0.2 percent to 36,688.12.    America Movil  SAB (AMXL MM), the wireless carrier
controlled by billionaire  Carlos Slim , slipped 0.2 percent to
33.55 pesos. The company offered to buy the remaining 571
million Telmex Internacional SAB shares it doesn’t already
control for 11.66 pesos apiece, according to a filing yesterday
to Mexico’s stock exchange.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO), the largest cement maker in the
Americas, advanced 1.7 percent to 10.68 pesos. Crude oil fell as
members of the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries
discussed whether to hold a special meeting, easing concerns
that high  oil prices  may slow growth and curb demand for
building materials.  Grupo Aeroportuario del Sureste SAB (ASURB MM), the
operator of airports in southern Mexico, climbed 1.6 percent to
67.26 pesos. Cia. Mexicana de Aviacion, the country’s biggest
airline by passengers before it parked its planes, has proposals
from five groups interested in restarting the airline that
sought protection from creditors last year, said Gerardo Badin,
the court-appointed bankruptcy mediator.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
